features: 2 FOODS, 2 WAYS, AT THE SAME TIME: Eliminating back-to-back cooking like a traditional single-basket air fryer with 2 independent XL air fryer baskets.
SMART COOK SYSTEM: Achieve the perfect doneness, from rare to well-done, at the touch of a button with the integrated Foodi Smart Thermometer—no guesswork required.
DUALZONE TECHNOLOGY: The Smart Finish feature, unlocks cooking 2 foods 2 ways that finish at the same time, or the Match Cook feature, easily copies settings across zones for full 10-qt. capacity.
IQ BOOST: Optimally distributes power across each basket to cook a 6-lb. whole chicken and side as quickly as possible when Match Cook or Smart Finish is not selected.
6 VERSATILE COOKING PROGRAMS: Air Fry, Air Broil, Roast, Bake, Reheat, and Dehydrate.
XL 10-QT. CAPACITY AND 2 BASKETS: Cook a main and a side at the same time for quick, large family meals, or cook up to 8 -lbs. of chicken wings with ease.
2 INDEPENDENT 5-QT. XL ZONES: They have their own cooking baskets, cyclonic fans, and rapid heaters.
FASTER COOKING: Cooks two 6-lb. chickens up to 30% faster than a traditional oven. Frozen-to-crispy meals in 30 minutes. Wide temperature range, from: 105°F–450°F.
EASY TO CLEAN: Includes nonstick cooking baskets and dishwasher-safe crisper plates.
WHAT'S INCLUDED: Ninja Foodi Dual Zone Air Fryer, Foodi Smart Thermometer, (2) 5 Quart Baskets, (2) Nonstick Crisper Plates & 15-Recipe Guide.
body.description: Meet the Ninja Foodi XL 2-Basket Air Fryer, that lets you cook 2 foods, 2 ways and finish at the same time. This bigger and faster air fryer has XL 10-qt. capacity and includes 6 versatile cooking functions. Not only is this great for large family meals and entertaining, but this air fryer also has DualZone Technology, IQ Boost, and Ninja’s Smart Cook System.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Our first air fryer. Family suggested we get the big one, so glad we did. Didn't think we'd use it much, lol, that was proven wrong, 3-4 times per week. Quick, crisp, flavorful, super easy to clean. Multifunction, not just air fryer mode. Easy to program, works better than advertised. I was a total skeptic about Ninja appliances but have a blender pro thing with smoothie cups, blender container and food processor container with a blade and dough blade, use it at least once per day for family of three. That's amazing, and this air fryer is amazing too. Made homemade 2 ingredient dough pizza pockets that were so much fun and quick. Homemade potato chips. Baked homemade ravioli. Crisped Brussel sprouts with onion and balsamic. The chicken!... Are you kidding me?! I'm not paid by anyone, I purchased with my own money and I just wanted to encourage others to go for it with the 10qt. It fits just fine on our 4' countertops with cabinets above. It takes up a little space but not that bad, especially since it's used so much. Prefer it to my electric double oven for most things. The shiny chrome-like coating on the basket handles came off after two washes in the dishwasher with the strongest cascade pods, just faded away and now the silver is white plastic...oh well, don't care, it looks fine and the rest of the units features and performance makes that insignificant at best. The 10 qt makes it possible to cook enough for a family of 2-6 in one batch. Just get it.

reviews.reviewText: I read all the reviews before buying this. Some people reported that it was slower because they were two drawers. Other people reported that it didn’t heat up as well. I have been using this for a little over six months and It is a very good product. You can use it so that it completes the food together or completes the food at separate times. It is super Easy to use and easy to clean. We throw it in the dishwasher every time and never had an issue. I use it nearly every other day. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Learning curve; could use category cook features
reviews.reviewText: We purchased this as an upgrade from our single basket Cosori air fryer. The biggest draw on this model was the dual baskets, which allow for cooking two different things at two different temperatures. We’ve cooked chicken strips and both cooked perfectly and I’m very little time. The biggest drawback however, is that despite the size and bulk of this dual cooker unit, the individual baskets are extremely small. Whereas our old single basket air fryer could easily fit for chicken breasts, only two will fit in one of these baskets, and definitely only one if the chicken breast is oversized. One of the biggest cons about this air fryer that differs from one of our favorite features of our old air fryer is also that there are not any real categories. Our single unit air fryer by Cosori features, photos of bacon, pizza, frozen foods, and other common items that made it very easy to cook something without dragging out an owners manual, or even looking at the directions on a bag of frozen french fries. The single unit cooks things very well and required very little thought in the process. this unit has no such functionality. Even after reviewing all three manuals that came with this unit, it was impossible to find any straightforward directions on cooking, frozen french fries, for instance. What might be written on the outside of the frozen french fry bag, is not always the standard for every unit. What works for my old air fryer would not work for the new one. we experimented and ultimately just decided to go with what we thought was best since there were no air fryer instructions on the particular bag we were using, and luckily everything worked out well. The frozen chicken strips did have air fryer, instructions, and although we did not cook them as long as the bag indicated, I was able to check them frequently, and this air fryer did a sufficient job. If I had to purchase this over again, I probably would not. For the bulk, and this unit is extremely large, and will take up a great deal of counterspace, so that’s something you should know going in, I expected larger baskets and more functionality. I have not tried the dehydrating feature, which is something our old unit didn’t have, but we were interested in, so once I do that I will update this review. Since we’ve only used this unit a couple of times, it is only been washed a couple of times. Both times I threw the baskets in the dishwasher, removing the pans that detached from within them, and tossing all of them into the dishwasher. Everything came out clean, but it’s difficult to say what the dishwasher will do to the nonstick finish over time.

reviews.reviewText: I am a little late to the air fryer fad, but nonetheless, I finally got this one after eyeing for awhile and it’s awesome! reviews.reviewTitle: La Freidora esta golpeada o mal ensamblada
reviews.reviewText: Al revisar este producto se nota en el panel de control, protuberancias como si estuviera golpeado, además en el botón de encendido le presionas a los costados y también prende. Requiero que se me cambie el producto. Ademas mi esposa noto que el empaque cuando lo entregaron estaba al revés y una de las cintas casi despegada. Deben de tener mas cuidado con lo que entregan, no son productos económicos, y deben cuidar la calidad de lo que ofrecen.
